Enjoy the last of summer, and know that we can't wait to see all of our students!

This morning the North Central District Health Department (NCDHD) released the first official NCDHD color coded "Risk Dial" for the counties in the district. This includes Holt County. You can access the NCDHD Risk Dial by clicking on this link: https://public.tableau.com/profile/heidi.hostert#!/vizhome/RiskDialCounties/Dashboard1

As you can see, Holt County is shown as yellow. If school was to begin today, O'Neill Public Schools would follow the yellow section of the Modified Learning Plan. The NCDHD color coded Risk Dial will be updated weekly. You can access this and other information on the North Central District Health Department's website. https://ncdhdne.wordpress.com/

July 13 at 8:54 AM ·

We will be hosting wrestling camp in the old gym this Friday and Saturday July 17th and 18th. Kindergarten through 4th grade students will be from 9-11 am both days. Caden Moore will be our clinician. This camp is FREE for all O’Neill area wrestlers. Registration will be from 8-9 am on Friday.

Camp for wrestlers grade 5-12 will be from 1-4 pm on those same days: July 17th and 18th. Reminder this camp is FREE for all area wrestlers and registration is completed at the door just prior to the start of camp. Call or text if you have questions (402)-340-5812. Please share this announcement on your social media as well. 🦅💪🏼

*Those attending camp are asked to bring they’re own water bottle.

O'Neill Community Foundation Fund
August 19, 2019 at 8:31 PM ·

Tonight OHS FCCLA member, Ally, helped sign up families with children in the O’Neill school system, that are ages birth to age 5, for Dolly Parton’s Imagination Library at tonight’s elementary school open house. This program provides a FREE age appropriate book EACH month delivered to the child. This wonderful program has been made possible in part thanks to a grant from the O’Neill Community Foundation Fund and generous donors. We are excited to see this project touch so many and help encourage the joy of reading.

Upcoming Seniors and parents of upcoming seniors,

Typically we have time to get together with next year's Seniors before the end of the year to talk about senior photos, but this year we won't be able to do that. Attached is a very important document that you will need to print AND share with whomever is going to take your senior pictures this summer/fall or when you plan your session. Your photographer will need to sign the form on the back. Students and their parents will also need to sign it, and students will need to submit it to Mrs. Gotschall next school year.

On May 12th this information was emailed to all of next year's OHS Senior Class, and this link will be posted on the school website as well.

Link to senior photo information form: https://drive.google.com/file/d/1gBZPe7ZXOjglsv3e9se7cGezWdphtDfi/view?usp=sharing

Parents and students! The O'Neill High School Yearbook is doing a special section that documents this new learning culture change during the COVID 19 Pandemic.

If you took any photos of yourself or your student during our school's closure due to COVID-19, we are asking for you to submit 1-3 to be included in a special section of this year's yearbook. Photos can be of students engaging in social distancing, helping with volunteer efforts, doing online learning, or engaging in new kinds of learning and creativity!

Though this virus does not define 75% of our school year, our school culture changed because of it in the 4th Quarter, and because a school's yearbook is a historic document, we would like to include a section that tells this story.

Here is the link! https://forms.gle/tKqJbsxDmPewWCDY6

post_text: Hello this is Amy Shane. I am writing to let you know that after conversations with the Nebraska Department of Education and the North Central District Health Department, O'Neill Public Schools is suspending normal operations on our school campuses. Beginning April 1st, all education for the remainder of the year will be delivered via alternate means, either e-learning or packets. Until that time, students should continue the enrichment work assigned by their teachers. We will continue to communicate important information via calls, e-mails and social media. We will miss seeing your students in person, but look forward to continuing their education remotely.

shared_text:
Holt County News
March 20 at 10:00 AM ·

CONGRATULATIONS! Christopher Jennings, a junior at O'Neill, has won a Nebraska Young Artist Award from the University of Nebraska-Lincoln's Hixson-Lied College of Fine and Performing Arts. The awards recognize 11th-grade students from Nebraska for their talents in visual art, dance, music, theatre and emerging media. Jennings's specialty area is music.

Fifty-nine students from more than 40 high schools across the state have been selected as award winners. Students applied for the recognition and submitted an example of their work. Applications were received from 122 students. Hixson-Lied College of Fine and Performing Arts faculty chose the winners.

shared_text:
DQ Grill & Chill of O'Neill, NE
March 17 at 12:57 PM ·

As we all know, schools in O’Neill will be closed temporarily in an attempt to control the spread of the COVID-19 virus. This will present many challenges to families in our communities, including the possible lack of regular meals. We’d like to offer FREE takeout sack lunches on Saturdays & Sundays for students in our area schools!

Here are the details:

- 11am-2pm, Saturdays & Sundays through APRIL 5th (this may extended depending on our school district’s closure dates)

- ANY area student in grade PK-12 (one per student)

- Absolutely no purchase necessary!!

- Just DRIVE-THRU or STOP IN and order the SACK LUNCH SPECIAL!!

- SACK LUNCH SPECIALS include either a hot dog or cheeseburger with French fries and an additional side (additional side will vary depending on supply)

post_text: We want everyone to know that O'Neill Public Schools is staying in close contact with the North Central District Health Department to monitor concerns with COVID 19. We are observing all of the sanitation and preventative measures that have been recommended by the CDC. School staff is working on plans to educate students from home should it become necessary to close our schools. Students with compromised immune systems and/or students whose guardians have high risk health conditions may contact school nurse Stephanie Prouty.

post_text:
Congratulations to our Students of the Week,

COOPER HOFFMAN!

Cooper went along to the State Robotics Championship to help out the other teams. He helped keep them organized and made sure they were to their matches on time. Cooper also kept jumping in to help set up the game fields after the matches, even after matches that our teams were not competing in. At the end of the meet, he was helping the tournament hosts take down and pack up the practice fields. Cooper did all of this without being asked. Great example of the O'Neill Way.

Once again, congratulations to Cooper!

Be on the lookout for the next Student of the Week form! Here's to the O'Neill Way!

-Kelsey Osborne, 2021, EEB

Eagle Eye Broadcasting
March 2 at 10:05 AM ·

Congratulations to our Students of the Week,

ALYSSA MOSER, KELSEY OSBORNE & ZELIE SORENSEN!

Alyssa earned TWO first place medals at Howells-Dodge on Friday, February 21! One of those was her Humorous Prose, and the other was for her OID. Her hard work with coaches and at home is definitely shining through!

Kelsey's piccolo solo on Stars And Stripes Forever was the highlight of the Band Concert. Many in the audience complimented her outstanding performance.

Zelie's group was cooking in FCS, and Zelie decided to do the messy dishes by herself as the rest of the group was trying to finish up cooking.

Once again, congratulations to Alyssa, Kelsey, and Zelie!

Be on the lookout for the next Student of the Week form! Here's to the O'Neill Way!

-Kelsey Osborne, 2021, EEB

Congratulations to our Student of the Week,

MALLORIE SCOTT!

Mallorie earned herself the 1st place medal in JV Persuasive speaking at David City this past weekend. This was her first speech medal ever and she came home the champion! Her hard work is paying off!

Once again, congratulations to Mallorie!

Be on the lookout for the next Student of the Week form! Here's to the O'Neill Way!

-Kelsey Osborne, 2021, EEB
Nicole Keeler Scott Jon Scott

post_text:
Due to the Todd Becker Assembly scheduled for tomorrow (Wednesday) afternoon, the OHS State Wrestling PEP Rally has been scheduled for 9:30 a.m. on Wednesday morning 2-19-2020. The PEP Rally will be held in the new gymnasium (east side) and we ask that parents and public enter through the Activity Entrance. Let's send our state wrestling tournament qualifiers to Omaha with a lot of pride and excitement!

The NSAA State Wrestling Tournament schedule is attached. The Eagles will take to the mats this week on Thursday morning for first and quarterfinal round matches. You can check out more state wrestling tournament information at https://nsaahome.org/wrestling/
